May 5, 1929 D Nambour Contest (Special Oval March)
Nambour Contest (Special Oval March) 110 March Contest Nambour Contest nambour-contest-special-oval-march
Nambour, Queensland, Australia See http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/21403532
Run under a handicap system, whereby the scores of the Apple Tree Creek, Nambour, and Kandanga bands were each increased by 8 points. Both playing and marching were judged, with Mr Lawton judging the marching. This section was appended to the contest on the day.
Supplementary information from Dennis Mitchell, son of David Mitchell.
Nov. 15, 2011, 12:20 p.m. Nov. 15, 2011, 12:43 p.m.
1 Nambour Town Band P. Harrison March: First Parade
2 Apple Tree Creek Citizens Brass Band David Mitchell March: Victoria
3 Windsor Municipal Unknown March: Challenge
4 Kandanga District Unknown March: Knight of the Road
5 Gympie City Band Unknown March: The Victor's Return
